    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10376590>
    dc:description "FIGURES 1–12. Basic diagnostic characters of two subgenera of Phaeoxantha. 1–7—P. (Phaeoxantha). 1–3—male right mandible: 1—P. (P.) nocturna (Dejean); 2—P. (P.) laminata (Perty); 3—P. (P.) bifasciata (Brullé); 4–7—labrum: 4—P. (P.) nocturna (♂); 5—P. (P.) laminata (♂); 6—P. (P.) tremolerasi (W. Horn); 7—P. (P.) bifasciata (Brullé). 8—12—P. (Euphae- oxantha). 8–9—male right mandible: 8—P. (E.) wimmeri (Mandl); 9—P. (E.) klugii (Chaudoir); 10–12—labrum: 10–11—P. (E.) wimmeri (♂, ♀); 12—P. (E.) klugii." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10376590/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10376656>
    dc:description "FIGURES 161–164. Phaeoxantha (P.) bifasciata (Brullé), Moxos, Bolivia, ♂, 18.5 mm, LT (MNHN). 161—habitus, 18.5 mm; 162—labrum; 163—lateral view; 164—labels. Bars = 1 mm. Image credit Luboš Purchart." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10376656/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10376666>
    dc:description "FIGURES 173–179. Phaeoxantha (P.) bifasciata (Brullé), from Peru. 173—head, ♂, Rio Palcazu (COSJ); 174—labrum, ♂, ibid.; 175–176—aedeagus: 175—Rio Palcazu (COSJ); 176—Iquitos (JWCW); 177–179—elytron and details of its surface, Iquitos (JWCW). Bars = 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10376666/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10376670>
    dc:description "FIGURES 187–189. Phaeoxantha (P.) bifasciata (Brullé), ♀, ST of syn. “var.” obscura (Dokhtouroff), “Amazon” (SDEI). 187—habitus, 18.5 mm; 188—labels; 189—labrum. Bars = 1 mm. Image credit Kevin Weissing." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10376670/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10376672>
    dc:description "FIGURES 190–201. Phaeoxantha (P.) bifasciata (Brullé).190–196, 198–201—elytra: 190—♀, Brazil, Teffe (CCJM); 191– 192—ditto, details of surface; 193—♀, Brazil, Rio Solimoes (JWCW); 194–196—Bolivia, Rio Cesarsama (JWCW): 194—♀; 195—♂; 196—ditto, surface detail; 197—♂, aedeagus; 198–201—historical specimens ex Chaudoir (MNHN): 198—♀, as P. bifasciata; 199—ditto, surface detail; 200—♀, as “P. aequinoctialis”; 201—ditto, surface detail. Bars = 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10376672/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10376674>
    dc:description "FIGURES 202–211. Phaeoxantha (P.) bifasciata (Brullé), from Cabezas, Bolivia (COSJ). 202—habitus, ♂, 15.3 mm; 203— mandibles, ♂; 204–205—labrum: 204—♂; 205—♀; 206—maxillae, ♂; 207–211—elytra: 207–208—♂♂; 209—♀; 210 ♂; 211—ditto, surface detail. Bars = 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10376674/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10376678>
    dc:description "FIGURES 221–226. Phaeoxantha (P.) bifasciata (Brullé), from Orinoco, Venezuela. 221—habitus, ♂, 18 mm, San Fern- ando (CCJM); 222—mandibles, ♂, Tucupita (JWCW); 223–224—labrum: 223—♂, San Fernando (CCJM); 224—♀, Tucupita (JWCW); 225—pronotum, ♂, San Fernando (CCJM); 226—ditto, surface detail. Bars = 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10376678/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10376682>
    dc:description "FIGURES 235–240. Phaeoxantha (P.) bifasciata (Brullé), from Manaus—Rio Negro, Brazil (CCJM). 235—habitus, ♂, 14.5 mm; 236—head; 237—mandibles, ♂; 238–240—male labrum. Bars = 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10376682/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10376684>
    dc:description "FIGURES 241–249. Phaeoxantha (P.) bifasciata (Brullé), from Manaus—Rio Negro, Brazil (CCJM). 241—habitus, ♀, 18.5 mm; 242–249—male elytra and surface details. Bars = 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10376684/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10376742>
    dc:description "FIGURES 327–328. Biotopes. 327—Ecuador, SucumbÍos, Jivino river, locality of P. (E.) klugii – image credit Jan VybÍral; 328—Bolivia, Santa Cruz, Rio Yapacani, locality of P. (E.) wimmeri. Image credit Ondřej Šafránek." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10376742/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

